function findSecretSharers(n, meetings, firstPerson) {
    let secret_holders = Array(n).fill(-1);
    secret_holders[0] = 0;
    secret_holders[firstPerson] = 0;

    meetings.sort((a, b) => a[2] - b[2]);

    for (let [x, y, time] of meetings) {
        if (secret_holders[x] !== -1 && secret_holders[x] <= time) secret_holders[y] = time;
        if (secret_holders[y] !== -1 && secret_holders[y] <= time) secret_holders[x] = time;
    }

    return secret_holders.reduce((result, has_secret, i) => {
        if (has_secret !== -1) result.push(i);
        return result;
    }, []);
}
```


    The algorithm initializes an array `n` long with -1s called `secret_holders`, and only setting person `0` and the `firstPerson` to 0, representing that they initially have the secret. The meetings are then sorted by time. The algorithm then iterates over the meetings, and if either person `x` or `y` has the secret and the secret was obtained before the meeting time, then the secret is shared with the other person within this meeting. After all meetings, the algorithm returns the indices of `secret_holders` with values that are not -1, representing the people who have the secret.

